20/04/2011
VIENNA, Austria -- A court in Salzburg could rule on the extradition of former Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader on May 9th, when new hearings in the case are scheduled, local media reported on Tuesday (April 19th). The court is awaiting some documents from Zagreb concerning the extradition motion. Sanader has been in Austrian custody since December when he was arrested for suspected criminal actions and abuse of power in Croatia. (Austrian Times, Vecernji List, tportal.hr, Tanjug - 19/04/11)
